children.subject: I'm in a similar situation here (and wanted to piggyback on the thread). Would it be safe to enroll in 61c during adjustment?

history.content:
I'm planning on taking both of these classes next semester, but due to unit limits, I'll only be able to phase 2 one of these classes and enroll in the other during adjustment period.

Which of these would be safer to add during adjustment? 61C has 999 discussion and lab sections while Data 8 forces you to enroll in a corresponding lab section and I'm not sure if I'll get stuck with a bad time/all the labs will fill up if I save it for discussion. On the other hand, I'd rather take 61C over data 8 and don't know if leaving it until adjustment would cause issues.

I'm currently leaning towards adding 61C during adjustment because berkeleytime seems to indicate that only around 80-90% of the class is filled by adjustment day 1 while data 8 reaches 95% by that point. Also, incoming freshmen are more likely to enroll in data 8 over 61c so it might make it easier to get in? However, I don't know if the  scheduling/room issues for these classes this semester will affect historical trends, and as said before, I'd rather be in 61c over data 8.
history.subject: Adding 61C or Data 8 during adjustment?
